track_notes: The underwood trail is a little less scenic and bypasses Macrae peak. I would not recommend this Trail just because you would be missing out on alot of awesome viewing opportunities. It is a nice route back when you are trying to get back quicker.
Awesome trail if you like climbing ove boulders rocks and up cliff ladders. Just a little over 2 miles but took me almost 3 hours to hike due to the terrain. Best trail for some great views.
This is what is described in the article by KW4JM
track_title: W4C/EM-002 via Daniel Boone Trail Off the BRP
